---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="How WindowPlant Lab creates, labels, updates, and verifies content during the traffic experiment."
  canonicalPath="/editorial-policy/"
>
  <article class="content">
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Every substantial page must solve a specific plant placement problem and include an original useful component:
      a calculator, checklist, decision tree, table, diagram, or measured dataset.
    </p>
    <h2>Evidence rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No fabricated personal experience, credentials, reviews, quotes, statistics, or customer stories.</li>
      <li>Factual claims that depend on external evidence should cite reliable sources before publication.</li>
      <li>Assumptions must be labeled and converted into testable improvements when possible.</li>
      <li>Images must be original diagrams, generated charts, project screenshots, or properly licensed assets.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Update rules</h2>
    <p>
      Pages with Search Console impressions, Cloudflare visits, or legitimate referrers are improved before publishing
      new content unless the daily bottleneck clearly points elsewhere.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
